        </p>

		<section>
			<title>Font Styles</title>
			<p>
				This section illustrates various font styles, such as <b>bold</b>, <i>italic</i>,
				<u>underline</u>, superscript<sup>1</sup>, subscript<sub>2</sub>, <foreground color="magenta">foreground colour</foreground>,
				<background color="yellow">background colour</background>, <size scale="0.7">font size</size>, and
				<font name="serif">font name</font>. The title of the document, which is substituted
				via a <font name="monospace">get</font> element is "<crossRef ref="doc" />". It's use is not restricted
				to the document, but may be used for any element. For example, the top-level section's title is
				"<crossRef ref="firstSection" />".
			</p>
			<equation>
				y = A sin(wt)
			</equation>
			<section>
				<title>Subsection</title>
				<equation>
					y = A cos(wt)
				</equation>
			</section>
		</section>

		<section>
			<title>Displaying Images</title>
			<p>
				This section demonstrates the different ways in which images can be displayed. They can be
				displayed independently, as the QUBE Servo is shown below, or images can be stored inline,
				as the image <image src="eqn_1b4ccd98877b4e34b2469066224e79f5.png" alt="T(s)" scale="0.02" baseline="3" />
				within this paragraph.
			</p>
			<image src="qube_servo.png" alt="QUBE Servo"/>
		</section>

		<section>
			<title>Changing Font Size</title>
			<p name="sizeParagraph">
	    		Here is some text whose size we wish to change.
	    	</p>
			<p>
	    		Move the slider below to change the size of the text. Press the button to reset
	    		the size to the default size.
	    	</p>
			<!--- Use CDATA here because of angle brackets inside script -->
			<slider name="sizeSlider" min="0.1" max="3" value="1">
				<onValueChanged><![CDATA[
					sizeParagraph.FormattedText = string.format("<size scale='%f'>Here is some text whose size we wish to change.</size>", value);
				]]></onValueChanged>
			</slider>
			<button content="Reset Size" onClick="sizeSlider.Value = 1"/>
		</section>

		<section>
			<title>Changing Font Color</title>
			<p name="colouredParagraph">
				<foreground color="0 0 127">Here is some text whose colour we wish to change.</foreground>
			</p>
			<p>
	    		Move the sliders below to change the red, green and blue components of the text colour. Press the button
	    		to reset the colour to black.
	    	</p>
			<!--- Use CDATA here because of angle brackets inside script -->
			<script><![CDATA[
				local red = 0;
				local green = 0;
				local blue = 127;

				function changeParagraphColour()
					colouredParagraph.FormattedText = string.format("<foreground color='%d %d %d'>Here is some text whose colour we wish to change.</foreground>",
						red, green, blue);
				end
			]]></script>
			<slider name="redSlider" min="0" max="255">
				<onValueChanged>
					red = value;
					changeParagraphColour();
				</onValueChanged>
			</slider>
			<slider name="greenSlider" min="0" max="255">
				<onValueChanged>
					green = value;
					changeParagraphColour();
				</onValueChanged>
			</slider>
			<slider name="blueSlider" min="0" max="255" value="127">
				<onValueChanged>
					blue = value;
					changeParagraphColour();
				</onValueChanged>
			</slider>
			<button content="Reset Colour" onClick="redSlider.Value = 0; greenSlider.Value = 0; blueSlider.Value = 0;" />
		</section>

		<section>
			<title>Changing Button Text</title>
			<p>
				This section illustrates changing button text each time the button is pressed.
			</p>
			<script>
				local switch = 0;
			</script>
			<button name="toggleButton" content="Press here">
				<onClick>
					switch = 1 - switch;
					if (switch == 0) then
						toggleButton.Text = "Switch is off";
					else
						toggleButton.Text = "Switch is on";
					end
				</onClick>
			</button>
		</section>
